Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Machine Learning Engineer - Agentic AI role with Apple. I bring over three years of professional experience building production software systems, LLM-driven agentic workflows, evaluation infrastructure, and backend integrations, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across engineering and AI research roles, I have built systems that directly match the end-to-end agentic system design this position requires. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed a production platform for scalable agentic systems using large language models (LLMs), LangGraph, LangChain, Langfuse, and FastAPI, translating product requirements from cross-functional teams into multi-step CRM workflows across 40+ specialized sub-agents. I also built tool use and structured outputs infrastructure by refactoring 500+ backend operations into typed tool-group dispatchers, replacing 60+ per-agent REST tools with validated interfaces that retrieve context, call APIs, and execute actions. That work required the same architectural tradeoffs Apple describes: balancing latency, cost, accuracy, and controllability while preserving reliable planning, tool routing, tenant-aware execution, and failure handling.

My work also aligns closely with the evaluation and production-readiness responsibilities of this role. At Sperse, I built monitoring and observability infrastructure with trace-driven eval suites and real-time monitors that replay production conversations across prompts and model versions, flagging unsafe agent behavior before release. At Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I built an agent-evaluation pipeline for computer vision and machine learning (CVML) experiments, using LLM judges and reward models to evaluate multi-step workflows, rank tool-use runs, and improve quality, reliability, and cost tradeoffs. I also implemented a LangGraph eval pipeline that selected high-performing traces and tuned prompts with adaptive, LLM-driven approaches, increasing tool-call success by 50%. Those experiences give me a practical foundation for improving agentic system behavior through iteration, measurement, and production feedback.

Apple's focus on creating technology that empowers people, along with its values around accessibility, privacy, inclusion, and collaboration, is a strong match for how I approach engineering. The VCV team's work on human-centric, real-time interaction systems requires reliable full-stack execution across models, tools, APIs, and data systems. I would bring hands-on experience with LLM-assisted coding, agentic workflow orchestration, CI/CD, AWS Step Functions, Lambda, PostgreSQL-backed data systems, and distributed coding-agent orchestration to help Apple build controllable, scalable agentic systems that serve users with the level of quality expected from Apple.

I have always been passionate about building powerful tools that empower people while respecting privacy, accessibility, and inclusive design. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

